# 🗺️ URL Shortener — Complete Project Roadmap

> **Who is this for?** Someone who wants to *build and understand* every line — not just copy-paste.
> **Goal:** A production-grade URL Shortener with Redis caching, analytics, and live deployment.

---

## 📦 What You'll Build (The Final Product)

```
User pastes a long URL → Gets a short link (e.g., short.ly/abc123)
Anyone clicks that link → Gets redirected to the original URL
Dashboard shows: How many clicks? From which country? Which device?
```

### Feature List
| Feature | What it does | Why it matters |
|---|---|---|
| Short code generation | Converts long URL → 6-char code | Core logic |
| 301 vs 302 redirect | Browser redirect types | HTTP knowledge |
| Rate limiting | Max 10 requests/minute per IP | Production thinking |
| Click analytics | Tracks geo, device, time | Data pipeline |
| Redis caching | Stores hot links in memory | Performance |
| MongoDB TTL indexes | Auto-deletes expired links | DB-level features |
| REST API | Clean endpoints | Standard backend |

---

## 🗓️ Your Learning Path (7 Phases)

```
Phase 0 → Setup & Understanding
Phase 1 → Database Design (MongoDB)
Phase 2 → Core API (Express + shortcode logic)
Phase 3 → Redis Caching
Phase 4 → Analytics Pipeline
Phase 5 → Rate Limiting
Phase 6 → Frontend Dashboard
Phase 7 → Deployment (Render + Vercel)
```

---

## 📁 Final Folder Structure (You'll build this piece by piece)

```
url-shortener/
│
├── server/                    ← Backend (Node.js + Express)
│   ├── config/
│   │   ├── db.js              ← MongoDB connection
│   │   └── redis.js           ← Redis connection
│   │
│   ├── models/
│   │   └── Url.js             ← MongoDB Schema
│   │
│   ├── routes/
│   │   ├── url.routes.js      ← /shorten, /:code routes
│   │   └── analytics.routes.js← /analytics/:code
│   │
│   ├── controllers/
│   │   ├── url.controller.js  ← Business logic
│   │   └── analytics.controller.js
│   │
│   ├── middleware/
│   │   └── rateLimiter.js     ← Rate limiting
│   │
│   ├── utils/
│   │   └── shortCode.js       ← Base62 encoder
│   │
│   └── index.js               ← Entry point
│
├── client/                    ← Frontend (HTML/CSS/JS or React)
│   ├── index.html
│   ├── style.css
│   └── app.js
│
├── .env                       ← Secrets (never push to GitHub!)
├── .gitignore
├── package.json
└── README.md
```

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack — Why Each Tool?

| Tool | Why We Use It |
|---|---|
| **Node.js** | JavaScript on the server — fast, non-blocking |
| **Express.js** | Minimal web framework — handle routes easily |
| **MongoDB** | Stores URLs, analytics — flexible schema |
| **Mongoose** | ODM — makes MongoDB easy to use in Node |
| **Redis** | In-memory cache — super fast lookups |
| **nanoid** | Generates unique short codes |
| **express-rate-limit** | Prevents API abuse |
| **geoip-lite** | Converts IP → Country |
| **ua-parser-js** | Parses User-Agent → Device type |

